[[!meta title="Numerous security holes in Tails 3.1"]]
[[!pagetemplate template="news.tmpl"]]

[[!tag security/fixed]]

Several security holes that affect Tails 3.1 are now fixed in Tails 3.2.

We **strongly** encourage you to
[[upgrade to Tails 3.2|news/version_3.2]] as soon as possible.

- Linux: [[!debsa2017 3945]], and *partially* fixes
  [[!debsa2017 3981]] (*not* fixed: [[!cve CVE-2017-7558]],
  [[!cve CVE-2017-12153]], [[!cve CVE-2017-12154]],
  [[!cve CVE-2017-14051]], [[!cve CVE-2017-14340]],
  [[!cve CVE-2017-14489]], [[!cve CVE-2017-14497]],
  [[!cve CVE-2017-1000251]], [[!cve CVE-2017-1000252]])
- Tor Browser:
  [MSFA 2017-22](https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/security/advisories/mfsa2017-22/)
- libsoup2.4: [[!debsa2017 3929]]
- git: [[!debsa2017 3934]]
- libgd2: [[!debsa2017 3938]], [[!debsa2017 3961]]
- libmspack: [[!debsa2017 3946]]
- libraw: [[!debsa2017 3950]]
- libxml2: [[!debsa2017 3952]]
- thunderbird (icedove): [[!debsa2017 3968]]
- tcpdump: [[!debsa2017 3971]]
- bluez: [[!debsa2017 3972]]
- perl: [[!debsa2017 3982]]
- samba: [[!debsa2017 3983]]
